The paper deals with games with reachability objectives, which are typically studied in the area of game theory (cs.GT). The use of energy constraints suggests a connection to the area of logic and verification (cs.LO), where energy games have been extensively studied. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and complexity, which are relevant to the areas of data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the formalism of games and their solutions, which is relevant to the area of programming languages (cs.PL).
